Healthcare industry: refers to companies involved in the provision of health care services, manufacturing of health care equipment, or development of health care-related technology and products; 
Earnings surprise: the difference between the actual earnings per share (EPS) and the estimated EPS, often used as a measure of a company's financial performance; 
Market capitalization: the total value of a company's outstanding shares, used as a measure of a company's size; 
Ticker symbol: a unique abbreviation used to identify a company's stock on a stock exchange.
